        },
        "body" : "For templates, \"observers\" is lexed as an identifier, not a keyword, and so requires additional `,`s to separate the various fields:\r\n```\r\n      (Id(\"precondition\") ~> expr) ~\r\n      (`,` ~> Id(\"signatories\") ~> expr) ~\r\n      (`,` ~> Id(\"observers\") ~> expr) ~\r\n      (`,` ~> Id(\"agreement\") ~> expr) ~\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhereas for choices we have this keyword style: `by`, `to`, which doesn't require commas.\r\n(this is why I went for a new `ob` keyword)\r\n\r\n```\r\n      `by` ~ expr ~\r\n      opt(`ob` ~> expr) ~\r\n      `to` ~ expr ^^ {\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you want to move to the identifier style, then we should probably also change keyword `by` to identifier `controllers` to be consistent, and so require commas between all the fields.\r\n",
        "createdAt" : "2020-10-20T10:30:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-10-21T08:55:23Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : {
          "login" : "nickchapman-da",
          "name" : null,
          "avatarUrl" : "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/49153372?v=4"
